    "ideation": "The eyeglasses animation personifies the act of 'nerding out' or intense intellectual scrutiny. It isn't just about vision; it's about the physical adjustment of spectacles and the moment of clarity. The sequence begins with 'fuzzy' vision—dilated, unfocused eyes and a wavy, uncertain mouth. Then comes the 'push': the eyes snap together (gaze_x) as if the frames are being nudged up the nose. This is followed by a dramatic sharpening: the eyes shrink into precise, high-contrast pupils while the lids level out into a serious, scholarly line. The mouth transitions from a soft wave to a perfectly flat, focused line of concentration. The color palette shifts from a blurry, muted lavender to a sharp, clinical cyan-white, representing the moment of high-definition comprehension.",
